instructions:
Ingredients:
4 slices of sourdough bread
1 tablespoon of butter
2-3 ounces of deli sliced turkey breast
Â½ of a red, yellow, or orange bell pepper
2 slices of provolone cheese

Instructions:
1. Preheat a panini press (or a stovetop grill/griddle pan) to medium-high heat.
2. Spread the butter on one side of each slice of bread. Place the slices of bread, butter side down, in the panini press. If using a stovetop grill/griddle pan, add butter to the non-stick grill/griddle.
3. Layer the two slices with the turkey, bell pepper, and provolone cheese. Top with the remaining two slices of bread, butter side up.
4. Close the press and cook for 5-7 minutes, or until the bread is golden brown and the cheese has melted.
5. Serve the panini warm. Enjoy!
title: Turkey, Bell Pepper & Provolone Panini

instructions:
Ingredients:
- 1 Tomato, diced
- 2 Eggs
- 1 Orange, peeled and segmented
Instructions:
1. Heat a small non-stick skillet over medium heat.
2. Add the diced tomato and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft and beginning to break down, about 5 minutes.
3. Crack the eggs into the skillet and season with a little salt and pepper.
4. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the eggs are cooked to your desired doneness.
5. Serve the eggs with the tomato and top with the orange segments. Enjoy!
title: Tomato, Egg, and Orange Breakfast

instructions:
Ingredients:
2 oranges, peeled and cut into wedges
3 small potatoes, peeled and cut into cubes
3 ripe peaches, peeled and cubed
1/2 cup cooked rice

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Toss potatoes in a bowl with some olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread potatoes onto a baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until potatoes are golden and crispy.
3. Peel and cube oranges and peaches and place in a medium bowl.
4. Once potatoes are ready, add to the bowl with the oranges and peaches.
5. Pour cooked rice into the bowl and mix ingredients together until evenly distributed.
6. Serve the Orange Potato Peach Rice Bowl warm!
title: Orange Potato Peach Rice Bowl

instructions:

4. Add the apples and oranges and sautÃ© for 3-4 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: Apple Orange Potato Scramble

instructions:
Ingredients: 
- 2 large potatoes, diced into small cubes
- 6 eggs
- 1/2 cup fresh spinach, chopped
- 2 tablespoons olive oil
- Salt and pepper to taste

Instructions: 
1. Preheat oven to 375Â°F.

2. Place diced potatoes on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Drizzle with olive oil, salt, and pepper, and mix to combine.

3. Bake potatoes in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until lightly golden and tender.

4. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl whisk together eggs.

5. Add spinach to the egg mixture and combine to incorporate.

6. Once potatoes are cooked remove from oven and turn oven to broil.

7. Add egg and spinach mixture to the baking sheet with the potatoes.

8. Place baking sheet back in oven and broil for 5-7 minutes, or until egg is completely cooked and lightly golden on top.

9. Remove from oven and enjoy immediately!
title: Oven Roasted Potato, Egg, and Spinach Breakfast
